## 7. Testing Conventions

### Unit Tests (Vitest)
```typescript
// src/modules/budgets/budget-health.test.ts
import { calculateBudgetHealth } from './budget-health';
import { expect, test } from 'vitest';

test('returns healthy for balanced budget', () => {
  const result = calculateBudgetHealth({ income: 5000, expenses: 4000 });
  expect(result.status).toBe('healthy');
});
```

### E2E Tests (Playwright)
- One spec per major flow
- Use `test.describe` for grouping
- Test auth flows in `welcome-auth.spec.ts` and `smoke.spec.ts`

### Test Commands
```bash
npm run test          # Unit tests (vitest)
npm run test:watch    # Watch mode
npm run test:e2e      # E2E tests (playwright)
npm run lint          # ESLint
npm run build         # Next.js build (type-checks)
```

