## 8. Common Pitfalls to Avoid

| Pitfall | Correct Approach |
|---------|------------------|
| Editing UI before finding domain module | Start in `src/modules/<domain>/` |
| Mixing root app and `budgetbitch/` prototype | Treat as separate systems |
| Skipping Convex guidelines | Read `convex/_generated/ai/guidelines.md` first |
| Using `.collect()` or `filter` in Convex | Use indexes + `withIndex` + `.take()` |
| Passing `userId` from client for auth | Derive server-side via `ctx.auth.getUserIdentity()` |
| Adding `'use client'` unnecessarily | Default to Server Components |
| Forgetting argument validators in Convex | Always include `args` with `v.*` validators |
| Not running tests before commit | `npm run test && npm run test:e2e && npm run lint` |

